     Programming news
     ----------------
    
û
        This section is set to inform you of currently known projects
    underway. This is so that you don't spend days on a project, only to
    find out that someone else has also done a version. If you want your
    program information included, then send it to me at the Mushroom PD
    address, along with an article for inclusion. Here is the current list
    of programmers, and what they are doing:
    
ü
      Paul Burkey
      -----------
    
ý
        Paul is currently updating his AmigaGUIDE reader - Smoothguide.
    The program will now read in guides that have been crunched with
    PowerPacker, or any XPK cruncher. He has also added italics and bold,
    and speeded up the whole access of the program. The program will not
    crash on an A500/600 anymore.
    
    
ÿ
