      Andrew "Mushroom" Kellett (That's me, dudes !!)
      -------------------------
    
ý
        At this moment in time, I am writing this document for EA Issue 3.
    I have also been working on Twinz Proffessional, a fully-upgraded
    version of the old Twinz game, with a brand new engine. Check the
    review in WAC 8. I am also adding the finishing touches to MMPlay GUI,
    my own fully-usable module player. It includes commands from MMPlay
    CLI, as well as a few more goodies. Simply point and listen. A
    demonstration version will be ready by the time you read this text,
    and will probably be on the coverdisk.
    
        Other projects that I am currently trying to finish, are Cardfile,
    a small WB utility which allows you to store information on a
    person/company, and view it with ease. You can also include pictures
    (if available). I am also trying to do a simulation of the C64 hit
    Commando. It is coming on very slowly, as I can't draw the soldiers
    very well !!!
    
